## 1. Introduction
This document presents the design, fabrication and testing of a real **Mars Rover prototype** developed for rough-terrain locomotion and exploration research. The objective was to design a stable, lightweight and modular rover capable of navigating uneven planetary surfaces.

---

## 2. Mission Objectives
- Develop a rover capable of traversing rocky and sandy terrain.
- Maintain structural stability using a rocker-bogie suspension system.
- Ensure modular components for easy maintenance and part replacement.
- Integrate a camera stand for future autonomous navigation upgrades.

---

## 3. Design Requirements
| Parameter | Target |
|----------|--------|
| Weight | Low weight for mobility |
| Strength | Sustain static & dynamic loads |
| Terrain | Capable of slopes, rocks & loose soil |
| Safety | No tipping at high tilt angles |
| Manufacturing | 3D-print compatible and low-cost |

---

## 4. Rover Subsystems
### 4.1 Chassis System
- Lightweight skeletal frame
- Maximum rigidity with minimum mass

### 4.2 Rocker-Bogie Suspension
- Six-wheel independent suspension
- Maintains balance on uneven terrain

### 4.3 Wheel & Rim Assembly
- Special tread geometry for high traction
- Suitable for sandy and rocky surfaces

### 4.4 Camera Mount Stand
- Adjustable height
- Ensures stable image capture

### 4.5 Body Materials
- PLA material for 3D printed components
- Stainless steel fasteners for joints

---

## 5. Testing & Validation
Testing was conducted to assess strength, durability and terrain performance.

### 5.1 Static Load Test (SLT)
- Evaluated deformation under applied load
- Results: Structure remained within design tolerance

### 5.2 Stress Test (ST)
- Assessed long-duration repetitive load
- No structural failure observed

### 5.3 Terrain Test
- Tested on gravel, mud and slopes
- Maintained stability without tipping

---



The rover demonstrated **excellent stability and ground clearance**, proving the effectiveness of the rocker-bogie mechanism.

---

## 7. Future Scope
- Integrate solar panel power system
- Add motorized locomotion for autonomous movement
- Add image processing and mapping capabilities

---

## 8. Conclusion
The prototype successfully meets the mission requirements for planetary surface exploration. Its modular design, stability and validated performance make it suitable for future research in autonomous navigation and robotic exploration.

